    • Constructor Detail

      • FitnessContributionTable

        public FitnessContributionTable(InfluenceMatrix inf)
        Internally create a 3-dimensional table, by N by 2 by 2^K, where N and K are from the influence matrix. Dimension 1 represents N elements. Dimension 2 represents the 2 choices (i.e. 0 or 1) for one element. Dimension 3 represents all the possible combination of one element's dependent elements. The value is a randomly generated fitness contribution value between 0 to 1. E.g., when N = 6 and K = 5, the value in [0][1][5] gives the fitness contribution value when "the 0th element" is "1" given "its 5 dependent elements are 0,0,1,0,1 respectively". E.g., when N = 4 and K = 2, the value in [1][0][1] gives the fitness contribution value when "the 1st element" is "0" given "its 2 dependent elements are 0,1 respectively".
        Parameters:
        inf - an influence matrix object
